  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [ ] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\n_No response_\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\n_No response_\n\n### Operating System\n\nNone\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nI see `ETH_RPC_URL` in the `RpcOpts`\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#[derive(Clone, Debug, Default, Parser)]\r\npub struct RpcOpts {\r\n    /// The RPC endpoint.\r\n    #[clap(short = 'r', long = \"rpc-url\", env = \"ETH_RPC_URL\")]\r\n    pub url: Option<String>,\r\n```\r\n\r\nBut it does not work for me, afaics the only way to get forge to actually use it is like `forge script --rpc-url \"$ETH_RPC_URL\"` which doesn't seem right to me.\r\n\r\nI expect that when i use the environment variable defined in the config that i don't also have to pass it to the flag for the same option.",
